# API Design Standards

## Endpoint Naming

RESTful resource naming with version prefix:

```
GET    /api/v1/bookings          — list (paginated)
POST   /api/v1/bookings          — create
GET    /api/v1/bookings/:id      — read
PUT    /api/v1/bookings/:id      — update
DELETE /api/v1/bookings/:id      — delete
```

Never use verb-based names (`/getBookings`, `/createBooking`).

## Response Envelope

All responses follow this structure:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": { "id": "123", "status": "confirmed" },
  "meta": { "timestamp": "2026-02-15T16:00:00Z" }
}
```

Errors:

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
    "message": "Invalid phone number",
    "details": { "field": "phone", "reason": "Must be 7 digits" }
  }
}
```

## Requirements

- Version all endpoints (`/api/v1/`)
- Paginate list endpoints (cursor or offset-based)
- Rate limit public endpoints
- Correct HTTP status codes (201 create, 204 delete, 4xx client errors)
- Consistent error envelope on all failure responses
